* She plowed down the halls, turning corner after corner, but somewhere in 
this maze of a ship she had gotten turned around. The halls didn't look 
familier anymore, and she knew that she might have to retrace her steps to 
get into the right one again. But to do that she would have to run into 
Prowl again, and if he saw her barreling towards him he might not 
move...trying to stop her.
Which wouldn't happen, that was a fact.
She may not be too big but she was stronger then before, even her second 
beast mode couldn't handle the merged modes alone.

But if she didn't find a way back to familier halls soon, she just might 
have to pass Prowl. Which she hoped she wouldn't have to do.
However, as she rounded a corner she planted her feet firmly...to prevent 
from smashing into the wall!
DEAD END!!

But she couldn't manage to stop herself in time and clenched her jaw as she 
slammed shoulder first into the wall...with the force of a being thrown my a 
50ft tall transformer!
Yes, there was a dent in the wall where she hit, and a little bit of 
yellowish mech-fluid as well. But she sound of the sickening CRACK as she 
hit was the worst of all.
If it had been any other creature it would have died on impact...but she had 
only dislocated her shoulder.

She stepped back from the wall and turned towards the hall again, knowing 
that Prowl would be there any moment. And with this shoulder she could make 
it at a bare run, but one slow enough that a bot could easily run beside 
her.
She watched for Prowl as she hobbled a bit on her bad leg, though looking 
for a section of the walls which would due perfectly for relocating her 
shoulder.
She may have the mind of a beast now, but she remembered her training as a 
bot.*
